what really happened.

190
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:39,820
Wait, she didn't tell you?

191
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:43,300
You always tell her everything.

192
00:12:46,380 --> 00:12:47,660
Can't blame her for that.

193
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:49,620
Maybe Wen Zhiqiu

194
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:51,060
hurt her somehow,

195
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:52,940
and she's not ready
to talk about it yet.

196
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,260
Maybe she never thought of you

197
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,660
as a real friend.

198
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:03,780
Is this bag custom-made?

199
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:04,740
Yes.

200
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:08,140
Men

201
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:10,460
are always two-faced.

202
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,380
None of you can be trusted.

203
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:16,820
Give me the biggest diamond ring.

204
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:17,540
Okay.

205
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,900
Not even me?

206
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:27,460
Maybe today,

207
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,340
but tomorrow?

208
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:31,140
I wouldn't bet on it.

209
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:32,540
Bring me the necklace.

210
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:47,020
So?

211
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:48,860
How do I look?

212
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:53,620
Stunning.

213
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:56,940
I want everything Miss Bai picked out.

214
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:58,500
No.

215
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:04,820
What do you mean?

216
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,540
I don't want any of these.

217
00:14:09,060 --> 00:14:10,100
Not a single one?

218
00:14:10,780 --> 00:14:11,660
Yes.

219
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:17,100
What do you want?

220
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:21,020
I want you to take me under your wing

221
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:22,460
and teach me the business.

222
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:25,980
Learning all that is so tiring.

223
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,540
Whatever you want,

224
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:29,340
just name it,

225
00:14:29,860 --> 00:14:30,980
and I'll get it for you.

226
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:33,500
You're only saying that
because you like me.

227
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:36,140
The day you stop caring,

228
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:38,020
even a newspaper might feel like
too much to spend on.

229
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:39,380
I need to be ready

230
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,420
for that day.

231
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:43,300
Alright.

232
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:46,820
Then you'd better start saving up

233
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:49,020
while I still like you.

234
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,420
Learning how to make money

235
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,300
is way more valuable.

236
00:15:01,180 --> 00:15:03,660
You're a lot more interesting
than I expected.

237
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:06,740
And if you keep teaching me,

238
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,060
I might just surprise you even more.

239
00:15:09,740 --> 00:15:10,420
Alright.

240
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:14,300
Here's your first lesson.

241
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:15,820
In business,

242
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:17,740
never trust anyone

243
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,220
but yourself.

244
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:23,380
Everything else can be an illusion.

245
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:24,700
Money's the only thing

246
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:27,180
that's real.

247
00:15:35,620 --> 00:15:36,420
Cheng Hui.

248
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:37,620
Shaohua.

249
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:39,020
Shaohua.

250
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:42,820
Shaohua.

251
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:46,580
You've gotten taller.

252
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:48,940
And you seem to have matured.

253
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:56,820
Shaohua.

254
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:00,860
This is my pharmacy certificate.

255
00:16:02,180 --> 00:16:03,620
Here's my chemistry qualification.

256
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:08,020
And this one is for my patent.

257
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,460
Shaohua, I didn't let you down.

258
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,180
I've been waiting for you.

259
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,180
This used to be a flour mill,

260
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:29,340
but due to poor management,

261
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:30,660
it went out of business three years ago.

262
00:16:38,820 --> 00:16:40,300
If we convert it
into a pharmaceutical factory,

263
00:16:41,020 --> 00:16:42,300
the building's structure can stay,

264
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:45,140
but we'll need to replace

265
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:46,620
all the partitioning, renovation,
and equipment.

266
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:48,020
Certainly.

267
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:53,020
This area can be converted

268
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:55,420
into a full herbal processing zone,
with a storage room,

269
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:56,380
a sorting room,

270
00:16:56,740 --> 00:16:57,580
a slicing room,

271
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:58,580
a processing room,

272
00:16:59,060 --> 00:16:59,980
a testing room,

273
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,100
and a packaging room.

274
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:03,740
Those sections in the back

275
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,020
can be turned into laboratories
and R&D rooms.

276
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:07,180
How much

277
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:09,420
will the entire reconstruction cost?

278
00:17:10,580 --> 00:17:11,580
Based on this scale?

279
00:17:11,980 --> 00:17:12,540
Yes.

280
00:17:13,260 --> 00:17:15,540
We're building a pharmaceutical factory

281
00:17:15,540 --> 00:17:17,420
that can truly achieve
Western-style processing of TCM.

282
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:20,540
We'll need
a full set of chemical instruments,

