00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:22,340
including specialized equipment
of all scales, from abroad,

284
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,180
and they have to be the latest models.

285
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:29,500
We'll also need a distillation machine,

286
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:32,500
a salve dryer, a powder grinder,

287
00:17:32,980 --> 00:17:34,300
two pill-making machines,

288
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:39,420
a steam-powered decoction furnace,

289
00:17:39,820 --> 00:17:42,060
a medicine cauldron, a slicing machine,

290
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:44,020
and some electronic equipment.

291
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:46,500
We'll need
at least 600,000 silver dollars.

292
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:48,060
That much?

293
00:17:48,820 --> 00:17:50,940
That doesn't even include
labor costs for chemistry experts,

294
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,820
pharmacists, engineers,

295
00:17:52,820 --> 00:17:53,540
administrative assistants,

296
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:55,020
and clerks.

297
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:56,660
But I only have

298
00:17:56,660 --> 00:17:58,300
a bit over 100,000 right now.

299
00:17:59,060 --> 00:18:00,740
Selling the house

300
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:03,300
might get us to 200,000.

301
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:05,060
That's fine.

302
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:05,940
We'll borrow the rest

303
00:18:05,940 --> 00:18:07,060
from the bank.

304
00:18:07,140 --> 00:18:09,140
Most factories overseas
are using this method now.

305
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:11,900
Back in the day,

306
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:14,540
all I needed
was a few dozen silver dollars

307
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:17,020
to get
tens of thousands of deals moving.

308
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,300
But that's no longer possible.

309
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:23,980
I can only get a little over 100,000
from the banks these days,

310
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:27,060
and the interest rates are insane.

311
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,620
If we don't use the latest equipment,

312
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,660
we could cut costs by at least a third.

313
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,100
No.

314
00:18:42,980 --> 00:18:45,700
If we're going to do this,
it has to be the most modern one.

315
00:18:49,380 --> 00:18:50,820
Then there's only one last way.

316
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:51,980
What way?

317
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:53,460
Shaohua,

318
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:56,100
you hold shares
in Wen's Pharmacy, don't you?

319
00:18:56,980 --> 00:18:58,980
Based on its current market value,

320
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,740
they should be worth
over a million silver dollars.

321
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:04,420
Under my agreement with him,

322
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:06,740
he holds the right of first refusal.

323
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:10,580
If I want to sell those shares,

324
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:13,300
I have to talk to him.

325
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:15,540
But I don't want to see him again.

326
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:16,740
Shaohua,

327
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:19,700
what happened

328
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,060
between you and Mr. Wen?

329
00:19:22,340 --> 00:19:24,100
You were still best friends

330
00:19:24,460 --> 00:19:25,700
when I went abroad four years ago.

331
00:19:26,660 --> 00:19:27,740
How come you don't even

332
00:19:28,220 --> 00:19:29,780
want to say his name now?

333
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:34,020
Let's drop it.

334
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:35,820
No, I have to say this.

335
00:19:36,540 --> 00:19:37,660
I know better than anyone

336
00:19:37,660 --> 00:19:38,860
what you two went through.

337
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,900
You started a business, struggled,

338
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:42,180
and survived
life-or-death situations together.

339
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:43,940
You didn't

340
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,660
just weather storms together.

341
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:47,260
You stood by each other
with unshakable loyalty.

342
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,980
You trusted each other with your lives.

343
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:51,980
So no matter how big the issue is,

344
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:53,460
you should still be able
to talk it through.

345
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,140
Cheng Hui,

346
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:56,700
believe me.

347
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:59,500
If I've decided
to cut all ties with him,

348
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,580
I must have a good reason.

349
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:06,620
Alright.

350
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:09,500
So, are we still building

351
00:20:10,260 --> 00:20:11,260
the factory?

352
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:19,580
I need you to go talk to him

353
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:23,220
about the shares in Wen's Pharmacy.

354
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:25,300
Okay.

355
